hands_on_practices.solution:
1. The Euclidean Clifford algebra and generators  
$$\{\Gamma_a,\Gamma_b\}=2\delta_{ab}I_4,\qquad S_{ab}=\tfrac14[\Gamma_a,\Gamma_b].$$

2. Block form for $a,b\in\{1,2,3\}$  
$$\Gamma_a=\begin{pmatrix}0 & -i\sigma_a\\ i\sigma_a & 0\end{pmatrix}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
\Gamma_a\Gamma_b
=\begin{pmatrix}\sigma_a\sigma_b & 0\\0 & \sigma_a\sigma_b\end{pmatrix}.$$
Hence
$$[\Gamma_a,\Gamma_b]
=\begin{pmatrix}[\sigma_a,\sigma_b] & 0\\0 & [\sigma_a,\sigma_b]\end{pmatrix}
=2i\,\epsilon_{abk}\begin{pmatrix}\sigma_k & 0\\0 & \sigma_k\end{pmatrix}.$$

3. Explicit $S_{12},S_{23},S_{13}$  
$$S_{12}=\tfrac14[\Gamma_1,\Gamma_2]
=\tfrac{i}{2}\begin{pmatrix}\sigma_3&0\\0&\sigma_3\end{pmatrix},\;
S_{23}=\tfrac{i}{2}\begin{pmatrix}\sigma_1&0\\0&\sigma_1\end{pmatrix},\;
S_{13}=-\tfrac{i}{2}\begin{pmatrix}\sigma_2&0\\0&\sigma_2\end{pmatrix}.$$

4. Commutator  
$$[S_{12},S_{23}]
=S_{12}S_{23}-S_{23}S_{12}
=\bigl(\tfrac{i}{2}\bigr)^2
\begin{pmatrix}\sigma_3\sigma_1-\sigma_1\sigma_3&0\\0&\sigma_3\sigma_1-\sigma_1\sigma_3\end{pmatrix}$$
$$\quad
=-\tfrac14\begin{pmatrix}[\sigma_3,\sigma_1]&0\\0&[\sigma_3,\sigma_1]\end{pmatrix}
=-\tfrac14\,(2i)\begin{pmatrix}\sigma_2&0\\0&\sigma_2\end{pmatrix}
=-\tfrac{i}{2}\begin{pmatrix}\sigma_2&0\\0&\sigma_2\end{pmatrix} 
=S_{13}.$$

5. Extraction of $c$  
$$[S_{12},S_{23}]=1\cdot S_{13}\quad\Longrightarrow\quad c=1.$$
